              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Detailed Tool Reviews</h2>

      {tools.map((t, i) => (
        <div class="review-card">
          <div class="review-header">
            <div>
              <span class="review-rank">#{i + 1}</span>
              <h3>{t.name}</h3>
              {t.badge && <span class="badge">{t.badge}</span>}
            </div>
            <span class="review-price">{t.pricing}</span>
          </div>

          <p class="review-summary"><strong>Verdict:</strong> {t.verdict}</p>

          <div class="specs-grid">
            <div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">Ideal Team Fit</span><span class="spec-value">{t.teamFit}</span></div>
            <div class="spec" style="grid-column: span 2;"><span class="spec-label">Key Features</span><span class="spec-value">{t.keyFeatures}</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="pros-cons">
            <div class="pros">
              <h4>Pros</h4>
              <ul>{t.pros.map(pro => <li>{pro}</li>)}</ul>
            </div>
            <div class="cons">
              <h4>Cons</h4>
              <ul>{t.cons.map(con => <li>{con}</li>)}</ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

      <h2>Buying Guide: How to Choose</h2>
      <p>Selecting the right tool requires understanding your team's specific workflow. Here are the key factors to consider:</p>

      <h3>1. Methodology Compatibility</h3>
      <p>Does your team use Agile (Scrum/Kanban), Waterfall, or a hybrid approach? Software teams using Agile will find Jira or Linear indispensable. Teams that prefer Waterfall planning with Gantt charts might prefer Asana, Monday.com, or Wrike.</p>

      <h3>2. Consolidation vs. Specialization</h3>
      <p>Do you want one tool to rule them all? ClickUp and Notion offer all-in-one workspaces that combine docs, tasks, and whiteboards. Alternatively, you might prefer highly specialized tools that do one thing perfectly, like Linear for issue tracking or Basecamp for communication.</p>

      <h3>3. Scalability</h3>
      <p>What works for a 5-person team might break for a 50-person team. Ensure the tool you choose has the reporting, permissions, and workload management features required as your team grows.</p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
